The King to the Lieutenant of his town of Harfleur, and the Treasurer of the same town, and to all other officers in that place, and every of them, greeting. Whereas we are given to understand that you have caused to be arrested divers victuals belonging to our beloved and faithful John Fastolf, in the town aforesaid; we, for certain causes laid before uS, in our proper person, do command you to release, without delay, all and singular those victualS, of whatever nature they may be, and to deliver them to the aforesaid John, or his attorney in that behalf. Witness the King, at his castle of Caen, in his duchy of Normandy, the Qd day of October.
